<apex:outputPanel styleClass="textBody">
<p>Dear Prospective Applicant,<br/>
<br/>
Conservation ultimately comes down to people – their behaviors toward nature, their beliefs about its value, 
and their ability to protect it without sacrificing basic life needs. 
Nowhere are community-based solutions needed more than in the Philippines; 
and area rich in natural resources, but poverty is also high, making social and environmental change a 
challenge for hundreds of communities. Rare and its partners in 50+ countries throughout Latin America, 
the Caribbean, Africa, Asia and the Pacific islands are committed to designing conservation programs that benefit 
both people and nature – ensuring that change is embraced and sustained. While Rare sources solutions, 
it does not directly implement outreach at the local level. Changing behaviors requires a nuanced understanding of 
social and cultural norms and trusted messengers from within each community. Therefore, Rare trains local partners 
and supports them during all stages of implementing what’s known as a “Pride campaign.” A Pride campaign inspires 
people to take pride in the species and habitats that make their communities unique, 
while also giving them alternatives to environmentally destructive behaviors.   
<br/>
<br/>Submitting this Expression of Interest  form is required and is the first step in the application 
process for the Rare Pride Program but does not commit you or your organization to any further action. 
Once you submit this form, you will receive a confirmation acknowledging that we have received your information. 
We will contact you two weeks after you receive the notice through an email or phone call to discuss next steps. 
If you have not heard from us within two weeks, or have additional questions, please contact Brooke Sadowsky, 
Pride Program Manager at bsadowsky@rareconservation.org.
 
<br/>
</p>
<p>We are anticipating the receipt of your expression of interest in running a Pride 
campaign at your site on or before  <b>July 31st 2011.</b></p>
